The paper deals with compressed sensing (CS) and source coding, which are both topics covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the reconstruction of a sparse signal, which is a common problem in Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of CS in image processing (cs.CV) and compares the proposed algorithms to existing schemes, which suggests a focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG).
